# Privacy Policy — SpeedDial Board

_Last updated: July 2026_

SpeedDial Board is a new-tab dashboard extension. This policy explains what data the extension accesses, where it goes, and what stays on your device.

## Summary

SpeedDial Board does not collect, sell, or transmit your personal data to any server we operate. We don't run any backend — the extension talks directly to your browser's local storage and to a small number of third-party APIs needed for specific features, listed below.

## Permissions and why they're needed

| Permission | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `bookmarks` | Read and organize your bookmarks into the speed-dial grid and collections. |
| `storage` | Save your preferences (grid layout, widget visibility, time format, search engine choice) locally in your browser. |
| `unlimitedStorage` | Allows storing larger data locally, such as an uploaded video wallpaper, without hitting default browser storage caps. |
| `tabs` | Open multiple bookmarks at once via "Open all in new tabs." |
| `history` | Show matching entries from your browsing history in the search-suggestions dropdown. |
| `geolocation` | Get your approximate location to show local weather. You can decline this and enter a city manually instead. |

## Data storage

All of the following is stored **only on your device**, using `chrome.storage.local` or IndexedDB (for larger files like video wallpapers). None of it is sent to us or any server we control:

- Your bookmark folder structure and speed-dial layout
- Grid density, widget visibility/size, time format, and search engine preference
- Recent search queries (used to power the local suggestions list)
- Uploaded wallpaper images or videos
- To-do list items

You can clear any of this at any time by removing the extension or clearing its storage via `chrome://extensions`.

## Third-party requests

Some features require sending a request directly from your browser to a third-party service. These requests are made straight from your device to the third party — SpeedDial Board itself never sees or stores the data in transit.

| Feature | Service contacted | Data sent |
|---|---|---|
| Weather | Open-Meteo (`api.open-meteo.com`) | Latitude/longitude (from geolocation or your manually entered city) |
| Manual city weather lookup | Open-Meteo Geocoding (`geocoding-api.open-meteo.com`) | The city name you type |
| Web search suggestions | Google Suggest (`suggestqueries.google.com`) | The text you've typed in the search bar, as you type it |
| Performing a search | Google, Bing, or DuckDuckGo (whichever you've selected) | Your search query, same as typing it into that engine's own search box |

None of these third-party services are controlled by us, and their use of your data is governed by their own privacy policies.

## Changes to this policy

If SpeedDial Board's permissions or data handling change, this document will be updated accordingly.

